SIMPLE: sententious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sententious
<hw>Sen*ten"tious</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos><ety>[L.
<ets>sentenciosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>sentencieux</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Abounding with sentences, axioms, and maxims; full of
meaning; terse and energetic in expression; pithy; <as>as, a
<ex>sententious</ex> style or discourse; <ex>sententious</ex>
truth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How he apes his sire,⟦br⟧
Ambitiously <qex>sententious</qex>!</q> <rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Comprising or representing sentences;
sentential.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Sententious</xex>
marks.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Grew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Sen*ten"tious*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Sen*ten"tious*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sentery</ent>⟦br⟧
